SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 958
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Jerry Beavers for his
contributions to the State of Tennessee.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Jerry Beavers, a highly respected member
of his community who has dedicated himself to improving the quality of life for his fellow citizens;
and
WHEREAS, born on August 5, 1948, in Dalton, Georgia, Mr. Beavers graduated from
Dalton High School in 1967, attended Trevecca Nazarene University, and served his country in
the United States Air Force and the Tennessee Army National Guard; and
WHEREAS, Jerry Beavers and his wife, former Senator Mae Beavers, whom he met at
Trevecca Nazarene University, are the proud parents of two sons, Eric David (Wendy) Beavers
and Jason Andrew (Angela) Beavers, and grandparents of Leighton, Blake, and Brayden; and
WHEREAS, in 1990, Jerry Beavers encouraged his wife to run for the Wilson County
Commission; he single-handedly knocked on doors after work to help get his wife elected, and
in 1994, he knocked on doors and put out signs in a three-county, ninety-mile-long district to
help her win election to the Tennessee House of Representatives. He again helped his wife's
election, this time to the State Senate, by knocking on doors across eight counties within the
State; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Beavers joined others in 2001 at the State Capitol to protest a possible
state income tax, while his wife led the fight inside the Capitol; and
SJR0958
