- 1 -

WHEREAS, Jerry Beavers retired from the United Parcel Service in 2007, after thirty-
eight and a half years of devoted service; and
WHEREAS, throughout the years, Mr. Beavers continued to participate in the political
arena through active campaigning during every presidential election, passing out signs in
Wilson County, and providing a headquarters for the campaigns; and
WHEREAS, in 2016, Jerry Beavers was elected as a Trump delegate to the Republican
National Convention in Cleveland, Ohio, and again in 2020; he supported the 2016 Trump
campaign by renting a building and ensuring there was a Trump Headquarters in Wilson
County; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Beavers ran for and was elected to the Tennessee Republican Party
State Executive Committee in 2018 and 2022; and
WHEREAS, even though he has retired, he will continue to support and help the
Republican Party and its candidates; and
WHEREAS, Jerry Beavers epitomizes the spirit and commitment to service and
community that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly acknowledge
and applaud Mr. Beavers for his dedication to the State of Tennessee and its citizens; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Jerry Beavers for his
service to his community, the Republican Party, and the State of Tennessee and extend to him
our best wishes for much continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
